<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1566313-this-book-seems-related-to-her-earlier">This book seems related to her earlier books Something Borrowed etc but I cannot work out where it sits in the timeline, and are all her books concerned withe the same people.?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1566313'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7114761-heart-of-the-matter">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1566313-this-book-seems-related-to-her-earlier">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1566313-this-book-seems-related-to-her-earlier">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1585789-katherine-nally"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1544556490i/1585789._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1585789-katherine-nally">Katherine Nally</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It’s in the future of the Something Borrowed timeline, maybe 5+ years, it’s not clear because it doesn’t matter. I don’t think the connection adds any<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It’s in the future of the Something Borrowed timeline, maybe 5+ years, it’s not clear because it doesn’t matter. I don’t think the connection adds anything at all to the story, it might as well be disconnected.<br /><br />No, not all of her books are about the same people.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
