<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/999420-nick-says-love-means-living-together-what">Nick says love means living together? What could,did he mean? Why does n&#39;t Tess ask what does he mean? They are living together,but he loved Valerie. Nick,Val and Tess know that. Then ?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_999420'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7114761-heart-of-the-matter">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/999420-nick-says-love-means-living-together-what">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/999420-nick-says-love-means-living-together-what">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/98009499-geovana-siqueira"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1567444097i/98009499._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/98009499-geovana-siqueira">geovana siqueira</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think Nick meant that love is the relationship, family, and life they had and what he felt for Valerie was just a vanity, a way to feel important an<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think Nick meant that love is the relationship, family, and life they had and what he felt for Valerie was just a vanity, a way to feel important and it was not love.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
