<span id="freeTextContainer15762870396331244511">In alternating, pitch-perfect points of view, Emily Giffin creates a moving, luminous story of good people caught in untenable circumstances. Each being tested in ways they never thought possible. Each questioning everything they once believed. And each ultimately discovering what truly matters most.<br/><br/>After Something Borrowed and Something Blue, this is my 3rd choice for Emily Giffin books. It was different and once again was rooting for a character I didn&apos;t think I would root for. I felt for Vale</span>
  <span id="freeText15762870396331244511" style="display:none">In alternating, pitch-perfect points of view, Emily Giffin creates a moving, luminous story of good people caught in untenable circumstances. Each being tested in ways they never thought possible. Each questioning everything they once believed. And each ultimately discovering what truly matters most.<br /><br />After Something Borrowed and Something Blue, this is my 3rd choice for Emily Giffin books. It was different and once again was rooting for a character I didn't think I would root for. I felt for Valerie and wanted her to come out on top. Ialso for some reason did not like Tessa but maybe I'm for the underdog. </span>
